## Desc

- openrc-init
  An init system (replacement for /sbin/init) included with OpenRC since version 0.25.0.
  https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/OpenRC
- runit
  a daemontools-inspired process supervision suite that also provides a program suitable for running as process 1.
  https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Runit
- s6 + s6-rc
  an init system built using components from the s6, s6-rc and s6-linux-init packages
  https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/S6
  https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/S6-rc
- sysvinit
  A collection of System V-style init programs originally written by Miquel van Smoorenburg
  https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Sysvinit
- systemd
  A modern SysV-style init and rc replacement for Linux systems.
- busybox-init
  suited to embedded operating systems, used by Alpine Linux, SliTaz 5(Rolling), Tiny Core Linux, and VMware ESXi, and used by OpenWrt before it was replaced with procd
- smss.exe
  Session Manager Subsystem, an equivalent in Windows NT


